                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1282.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Gonzales</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Sub-Secretary of State informs Scholle that Bobo, Haitian revolutionist, has
                    debarked at Santiago de Cuba after being refused admission at Santo Domingo. The
                    Cuban Government is having him closely watched as there are many Haitians in
                    Cuba and Government wishes to frustrate any revolutionary propaganda in
                    Cuba.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
